The paper deals with deep neural networks and their generalization across multiple domains, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of CNNs and classifiers suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), or multimedia (cs.MM). However, the focus on domain adaptation and generalization suggests that cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
